text:
I will start with the conclusion: this is not a 5 star resort. Even though most of the staff is friendly and well intentioned, the pool and beach area is nice, the rooms are quite large, there are a lot of things to improve:
1. They do not seem to consider that maintenance is important: one of the window sealing was suspended in the air, the shower water smells horrible immediately after turning it on, the shower hanger was broken, there is a gap between the floor and the door so if you leave the lights on in the evening you will have insects in your room, some part of the wall in our room was swollen, we had mould on our shower cabin, the paint on the blinds of  the shower window was peeling, there is no  isolation in the room so you can hear the footsteps of your neighbors or their conversations;
2. Cleaning is not their strongest point: one morning my tea mug had lipstick stains (they weren’t mine), we received in multiple days dirty or stained towels, the curtains in the room had staines on them, the only napkin provided at breakfast was dirty or had stains on it;
3. I asked for a late check out, at first they said it was not possible because the room needed to be prepared for the other guests. When I asked again they said they could extend it for 1,5 hours and if I needed more I had to pay USD 20 for 3 hours;
4. They didn’t deliver all the messages sent by the travel agent: some changes on the departure time occurred and no one told me (luckily, I called to double check and this is how I found out);
5. The breakfast is not that varied, it is ok for 4-5 days and for what they offer it is quite expensive (approximately USD 14 per person). Also, most of their prices are net of VAT, service charges and any other 
charges so it is hard to know how much an item in the menu costs.
